verses.roman:
eta bali' bhaṭṭa paḍilā prabhura caraṇe
kṛpā kari' prabhu tāṅre kailā āliṅgane

synonyms: eta bali'-saying this; bhaṭṭa-Veṅkaṭa Bhaṭṭa; paḍilā-fell down; prabhura caraṇe-at the lotus feet of the Lord; kṛpā kari'-showing him mercy; prabhu-Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; tāṅre-unto him; kailā-did; āliṅgane-embracing.
translation: After saying this, Veṅkaṭa Bhaṭṭa fell down before the lotus feet of the Lord, and the Lord, out of His causeless mercy, embraced him.
